CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959 reads: "Third Party - Thomas Dorin, of Erin St., testified in court that the chain of events which led to the fatal shooting of Emanuel Graham occurred after Graham became enraged upon finding Mrs. Graham and his (Graham's) six-year-old boy in Dorin's car. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Thomas Dorin, wearing dark hat, moustache, plaid shirt, long herringbone jacket, and dark pants, holding cigarette and posed in corridor of the Allegheny County Courthouse
